on came from England to Salem, MA, in 1644."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas de Weston Lord of Weston in Shire was born in 1305, in Shere, Surrey, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Weston, was 30 and his mother, Maud Westcott, was 13. He married Joan de Dewdeswell in 1328, in Shere, Surrey, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1305–":"1305–Surnud","1297–1337":"1297–1337","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1308–Female":"1308–Surnud","1333–Male":"1333–Surnud","1275–1320":"1275–1320","1292–Female":"1292–Surnud","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1333":"1333","1320":"1320","1275":"1275","1297":"1297","1292":"1292","1308":"1308","1328":"1328","Shere, Guildford, Surrey, England":"Shere, Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1305–":"1305–Kuollut","1297–1337":"1297–1337","1305–Male":"1305–Kuollut","1308–Female":"1308–Kuollut","1333–Male":"1333–Kuollut","1275–1320":"1275–1320","1292–Female":"1292–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1333":"1333","1320":"1320","1275":"1275","1297":"1297","1292":"1292","1308":"1308","1328":"1328","Shere, Guildford, Surrey, England":"Shere, Surrey, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1305–":"1305–Décédé","1297–1337":"1297–1337","1305–Male":"1305–Décédé","1308–Female":"1308–Décédée","1333–Male":"1333–Décédé","1275–1320":"1275–1320","1292–Female":"1292–Décédée","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1333":"1333","1320":"1320","1275":"1275","1297":"1297","1292":"1292","1308":"1308","1328